article.headline: Creighton 62, Northern Iowa 54
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Nate Funk scored 24 points and Anthony Tolliver added 17 as Creighton beat Northern Iowa 62-54 Friday. Creighton (11-5, 5-1 Missouri Valley) led the entire game, opening a 16-point lead midway through the first half and holding the Panthers to two baskets in the game's first 9 1/2 minutes. Northern Iowa (13-4, 4-2) trailed 28-15 at halftime and started the second half on a 10-2 run. Grant Stout, who scored 10 points, hit a jumper with 16:52 left to pull Northern Iowa within 30-25. Adam Viet's 3-pointer with 11:42 left cut Creighton's lead to 39-37. Creighton recovered with a 10-4 run, capped by Dane Watts' layup with 4:25 left, that extended its lead to eight points. Northern Iowa came within four points with 20 seconds left before Funk sealed the win with four free throws. Eric Coleman and Brooks McKowen led the Panthers with 13 points each.
